{"sequence":34,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:55:39.100886226Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-715cb334","body":"finding_summary: `PidRecordLiveState::RunningUnverified` is only honored in `interrupted_handoff_cleanup_candidate_with_dirs`; the rest of the liveness/recovery stack still collapses that state back to `false`/`Stale`, so a live legacy run can still be reclaimed when the process start time cannot be read.\nseverity: high\naffected_files: [\"src/adapters/fs.rs\", \"src/cli/run.rs\", \"src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs\", \"src/contexts/automation_runtime/cli_writer_lease.rs\"]\nremediation_hint: Thread the tri-state through every caller that makes reclaim/recovery decisions. `RunningUnverified` should block resume/stop reconciliation and PID-file reclamation the same way the new interrupted-handoff path does, rather than being treated as safely stale.\n\nEvidence:\n- `src/adapters/fs.rs:806-816` maps `RunningUnverified` to `false` in `pid_record_matches_live_process`, so existing bool-based callers cannot distinguish \"unknown\" from \"dead\".\n- `src/cli/run.rs:1563-1627` uses that bool to classify running snapshots; when it is `false` for a legacy record, the code falls through to `RunningSnapshotLiveness::Stale`.\n- `src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:771-773` and `:1676-1695` then treat the orchestrator as dead and reconcile a running snapshot to failed during resume.\n- `src/cli/run.rs:3722-3755` and `:4000-4012` allow `run stop` to take the stale-recovery path instead of refusing to touch a live-but-unverifiable legacy owner.\n- `src/contexts/automation_runtime/cli_writer_lease.rs:176-185` treats `!pid_record_matches_live_process(pid_record)` as reclaimable, so daemon lease cleanup can still delete `run.pid` for a live process in this state.","dedup_key":"212c43012a7e8121dfb72703d295899adc2d6d139765e6e2ef16847de5d33efe","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"codex","model_id":"gpt-5.4-xhigh","reviewer_id":"reviewer-1"}],"run_id":"run-20260414160444","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
{"sequence":35,"timestamp":"2026-04-14T16:55:39.109493821Z","event_type":"amendment_queued","details":{"amendment_id":"fr-2-0cf65d9e","body":"Three callsites still use `pid_record_matches_live_process()` which treats `RunningUnverified` as 'not alive' — same pre-existing behavior, but inconsistent with the bead's 'don't assume alive or dead' principle. Affected callsites:\n1. `orchestrator_process_is_alive` (src/contexts/workflow_composition/engine.rs:773) — could allow a second orchestrator to start if /proc or ps fails for a running process\n2. `run_pid_record_is_reclaimable` (src/contexts/automation_runtime/cli_writer_lease.rs:181) — could allow CLI to reclaim a daemon PID record for a running process\n3. `classify_running_snapshot_liveness_with_ignored_cli_lease_owner` (src/cli/run.rs:1563) — falls through to lease checking instead of recognizing the running process\n\nEach callsite needs its own analysis since the correct treatment of `RunningUnverified` may differ (e.g., orchestrator check should probably treat it as alive, while liveness classification might want a distinct return variant).","dedup_key":"4653c9c53d53dc6f50a38cf727728fd60e3fe8ea192e550e0810310edb9b1d66","reviewer_sources":[{"backend_family":"claude","model_id":"claude-opus-4-6-max","reviewer_id":"reviewer-2"}],"run_id":"run-20260414160444","source":"workflow_stage","source_stage":"final_review"}}
